#23900
The Measured Veil~
You stand within the Measured Veil, a place where fate itself is
portioned and restrained. The air is unnaturally still, carrying
a faint, luminous haze that softens the edges of everything it
touches. Beneath your feet, smooth marble stretches outward in
quiet perfection, unmarked by time yet subtly etched with fading
impressions of steps that never fully formed.
All around you, pale shapes drift at the edge of perception, echoes
of moments that almost were, lingering just long enough to be
noticed before dissolving into nothing. There is no chaos 
here, no urgency only a quiet, deliberate balance, as though every
possibility is being carefully measured and limited.
Ahead, the Veil thins into a silent hall where those unrealized 
paths begin to take form.
~
